columns.name: JOB_FILING_NUMBER
columns.description: A unique identifier assigned to a job filing. It consists of job number (a letter indicating the borough followed by an 8-digit number)  hyphenated with Filing Number (a 2-digit code identifying the filing type). Once the permit is issued, a suffix  "-EL" is added to the job filing number. (Example: M00000001-I1-EL)

columns.name: JOB_NUMBER
columns.description: A 9-digit identifier for the job. Should match the first part of the Job Filing Number. The first letter indicates the borough for which the filing is associated, followed by an 8-digit ID number

columns.name: FILING_NUMBER
columns.description: A 2-digit code identifying the filing type. Should match the last part of the Job Filing Number.

columns.name: FILING_DATE
columns.description: Date the filing was created. This should be the earliest date associated with this Job Filing Number.

columns.name: FILING_TYPE
columns.description: Indicates whether this filing is new, subsequent or Post Approval Amendment (PAA) filing

columns.name: FILING_STATUS
columns.description: Indicates the stage of this filing as it progresses through the permit application process.

columns.name: JOB_STATUS
columns.description: Indicates the overall status of the electrical job.

This dataset contains general information about the job filing, including location, applicant, type of work and fee information.
